<recipe>
    <name>Prawn and Pineapple Curry (KAENG KUNG PUT)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Put all the spice paste ingredients in a mortar and pestle and

pound to a paste. Alternatively, use a food processor and add 2 tablespoons water. Blend until well combined. 

HEAT the oil in a wok or saucepan. Add the spice paste and fry until fragrant. Stir in the coconut milk and cook for 2 minutes. Add the pineapple wedges, tamarind puree and kaffir lime leaves and simmer for 5 minutes, or until the pineapple begins to soften. 

ADD the prawns and stir well to cover them in the sauce. Simmer for 5 to 6 minutes until the prawns are cooked through. Stir in the fish sauce and sugar before serving.</instructions>
